<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1436,865,1826]" box="[151,630,865,889]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,865,889]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 7.20 mm., female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1436,865,1826]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,901,925]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Moderately large, robust species. General color of dorsum black and pale orange; forewings black with broad, translucent band below mesonotum, large pale orange spot on clavus, veins black with small pale orange spots; mesonotum and pronotum black, small, pale orange spots on pronotum; crown orange with pale yellow markings; eyes translucent (Plate VB); face with clypeus and ocellocular area orange, black stripe below eyes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1436,865,1826]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Head broad, distinctly narrower than pronotum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broad, slightly wider than eye, produced anteriorly about ¼ of entire length; foveate on each side of middle; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum slightly longer than crown, surface bullated; mesonotum large, about half again as long as pronotum; forewings long, broad, venation typical; clypeus elongate, broad, lateral margins broadly convex, median longitudinal carina distinct; clypellus about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, median longitudinal ridge inflated in basal 2/3.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1436,865,1826]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,1261,1286]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view small, subrectangulate, caudodorsal process very long, about equal in length of pyogfer body, slightly sinuate, apex trumpet shaped, caudoventral process very small, hooked apically (
<figureCitation box="[159,258,1333,1357]" captionStart="FIGURES 285–293" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1361,224,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-73@71.[200,1387,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 285–293. Docalidia zhangi, sp. nov. (285) pygofer, lateral view; (286) segment X, lateral view; (287) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (288) right style, lateral view; (289) right style, dorsal view; (290) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (291) aedeagus, ventral view; (292) connective, caudal view; (293) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281817/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 285</figureCitation>
); segment X long, broad apically, ventral process large with small curved process on ventral margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 285–293" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1361,224,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-73@71.[200,1387,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 285–293. Docalidia zhangi, sp. nov. (285) pygofer, lateral view; (286) segment X, lateral view; (287) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (288) right style, lateral view; (289) right style, dorsal view; (290) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (291) aedeagus, ventral view; (292) connective, caudal view; (293) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281817/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 286</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate, long, broad throughout, glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[872,973,1369,1393]" captionStart="FIGURES 285–293" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1361,224,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-73@71.[200,1387,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 285–293. Docalidia zhangi, sp. nov. (285) pygofer, lateral view; (286) segment X, lateral view; (287) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (288) right style, lateral view; (289) right style, dorsal view; (290) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (291) aedeagus, ventral view; (292) connective, caudal view; (293) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281817/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 287</figureCitation>
); right style long, longer than aedeagus, apophysis slender with large, triangulate, subapical flange (
<figureCitation box="[816,981,1405,1429]" captionStart="FIGURES 285–293" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1361,224,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-73@71.[200,1387,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 285–293. Docalidia zhangi, sp. nov. (285) pygofer, lateral view; (286) segment X, lateral view; (287) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (288) right style, lateral view; (289) right style, dorsal view; (290) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (291) aedeagus, ventral view; (292) connective, caudal view; (293) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281817/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs. 288, 289</figureCitation>
); aedeagus with shaft broad in basal 1/3, sinuate in lateral view with small subapical ventral process, gonopore basad of spine, large, exiting ventrally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 285–293" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1361,224,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-73@71.[200,1387,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 285–293. Docalidia zhangi, sp. nov. (285) pygofer, lateral view; (286) segment X, lateral view; (287) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (288) right style, lateral view; (289) right style, dorsal view; (290) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (291) aedeagus, ventral view; (292) connective, caudal view; (293) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281817/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Figs. 290, 291</figureCitation>
); connective broadly T-shaped, arms narrow, curved anteriorly at apex, membrane and medial ridge absent, stem short (
<figureCitation box="[368,466,1513,1537]" captionStart="FIGURES 285–293" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1361,224,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-73@71.[200,1387,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 285–293. Docalidia zhangi, sp. nov. (285) pygofer, lateral view; (286) segment X, lateral view; (287) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (288) right style, lateral view; (289) right style, dorsal view; (290) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (291) aedeagus, ventral view; (292) connective, caudal view; (293) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281817/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 292</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective short, strapped shaped, arising laterally in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1417,1513,1537]" captionStart="FIGURES 285–293" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1361,224,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-73@71.[200,1387,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 285–293. Docalidia zhangi, sp. nov. (285) pygofer, lateral view; (286) segment X, lateral view; (287) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (288) right style, lateral view; (289) right style, dorsal view; (290) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (291) aedeagus, ventral view; (292) connective, caudal view; (293) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281817/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 293</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
